brace
=====

Compatibility
-------------
- Arch Linux
- CentOS 7/8/Stream
- Debian 10
- Fedora 32/33 (preferred)
- openSUSE 15.2/Tumbleweed

License
-------
GPLv3 where applicable

Building
--------
- git clone [THIS REPO]
- Arch Linux: makepkg
- CentOS: rpmbuild -ba brace.spec --define "_sourcedir $PWD"
- Debian: dpkg-deb --build brace
- Fedora: fedpkg local

Contents
--------
	00-brace*				= GNOME/Cinnamon/MATE: change default settings
	30-nm-privacy.conf			= NetworkManager: enable MAC address randomization, disable connectivity checking, enable IPv6 privacy extensions
	60-restrict.conf			= kernel: restrict dmesg and ptrace
	blacklist-dma.conf			= kernel: blacklist modules that provide direct memory access externally
	blacklist-usbnet.conf			= kernel: blacklist modules that allow for USB networking
	brace-helpers.sh			= profile: adds helper aliases
	brace-installer.sh			= unified package installer
	brace-fedora-enable-auto-updates.sh	= Fedora: enables DNF automatic updates
	brace-fedora-remover.sh			= Fedora: package remover
	brace-fedora-update-system.sh		= Fedora: update system using dnf-plugin-system-upgrade
	brace-supplemental-changes.sh		= change extra default settings
	wireless-perf.conf			= kernel: increases wi-fi performance for b43 and iwlwifi
	userjs-*.js				= Firefox: change default settings

